# Backend standards

The backend uses a **layered** architecture (not feature modules). Each layer is
a top-level folder under `backend/src/`.

## Folder responsibilities

| Folder | Holds |
|--------|-------|
| `controllers/` | HTTP/SSE routing only; delegate to services |
| `services/` | business logic |
| `repositories/` | TypeORM data access (queries) |
| `entities/` | TypeORM entities |
| `dto/` | request DTOs + Swagger response DTOs |
| `interfaces/` | `interface` shapes (`I` prefix), barrel-exported |
| `guards/`, `decorators/` | auth + cross-cutting |
| `interceptors/`, `filters/` | response envelope + error normalization |
| `events/` | event-name constants for the in-process emitter |
| `modules/` | Nest module wiring |
| `config/` | typed env configuration |
| `database/` | migrations, seeds, and the TypeORM data source |

## Interfaces

- Do **not** define `interface` shapes inside `controllers/`, `services/`,
  `guards/`, `decorators/`, or `modules/`.
- Put `interface` shapes in `interfaces/*.ts` with an `I` prefix
  (e.g. `IApiResponse`), and export them from `interfaces/index.ts` — the only
  barrel in the backend.
- Other folders are imported by file path using **relative** imports
  (e.g. `../services/artifacts.service`). No `@/`/`@app` path alias is used.

## Layering

- Controllers: HTTP only. Apply guards (e.g. `@UseGuards(ApiKeyGuard)`) and
  return plain data — the global `ResponseInterceptor` wraps it. Mark SSE/raw
  routes with `@SkipSuccessWrapper()`.
- Services: own business logic; delegate persistence to a `*Repository`.
- Repositories: own all TypeORM access. Keep version assignment race-safe
  (retry on the unique-index conflict, as in `ArtifactsRepository`).
- Auth is a single shared-secret `ApiKeyGuard` (`x-api-key` header); there is no
  JWT/strategy/RBAC.

## Build & verify

```bash
cd backend && npm run build   # nest build
cd backend && npm test        # jest, co-located *.spec.ts
```

Swagger UI is served at `/docs`; the OpenAPI document is generated at runtime
(not checked in). There is no ESLint config in this package.
